      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. HDS Connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2909_3.0_jpn_11394437_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn ignition to ON mode. Connect HDS to the data link coupler (A) on the left side of the driver's seat. Verify that HDS communicates with the vehicle and ECU. If it does not communicate, Inspect data link circuits The following is a list of the most common problems with the",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "T002567",
          "label": "Inspect data link circuits",
          "resolved": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. ECU reset"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Select the PGM-FI system in HDS. When the engine is stopped, with the ignition in the ON mode, select ECU reset in HDS. Turn ignition OFF (LOCK) mode. Turn ignition to ON mode and wait for 30 seconds. Turn the ignition to the OFF (LOCK) mode and remove the HDS from the data link coupler."
